description: The election will rescheduled for 21 October if legislation is approved by the States.
title: Coronavirus: Guernsey general election delay proposed
title_page: Coronavirus: Guernsey general election delay proposed - BBC News
maintext: It would mean the current political term would continue until 29 October, to allow for the four-day election and counting the votes, with the nomination period for becoming a Deputy to be held between 14 and 18 September.
